The paper deals with unsupervised video segmentation, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel saliency estimation technique and a neighborhood graph, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques, respectively. Therefore, it is likely to belong to sub-categories such as cs.AI (artificial intelligence) and cs.LG (machine learning). The paper also evaluates its proposed algorithm on various datasets, which involves metrics and analysis, making it relevant to cs.MM (multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with motion and optical flow, which are relevant to robotics and control (cs.RO) sub-category.
